Grease a large cookie sheet. Set aside.

In a #heavy 2-quart saucepan{} over medium heat, bring @sugar{1%cup}, @corn syrup{0.5%cup}, @water{0.25%cup}, and @salt{0.25%tsp} to a boil. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Stir in @peanuts{1%cup}.

Set #candy thermometer{} in place, and continue cooking. Stir frequently until the temperature reaches 300°F (150°C), or until a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water separates into hard and brittle threads.

Remove from heat; immediately stir in softened @butter{2%Tbsp} and @baking soda{1%tsp}; pour at once onto the #13" x 18" rimmed baking sheet{}. With two #forks{}, lift and pull peanut mixture into a rectangle, about 14x12 inches; cool.

Snap candy into pieces.
